&lt;li&gt;Serve as a role model for participants as a young Jewish adult and an exemplary BBYO alum, translating past BBYO experiences into learning opportunities for participants. Display how the AZA and BBG movement meaningfully expands beyond high school years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with daily logistical needs, including but not limited to program set-up, supply organization, supply acquisition, supporting office tasks, supporting medical professionals, assisting with event preparation, catering to participants with unique dietary needs, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare the hotel for teen arrival in advance of August Execs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in informal education programming, &lt;em&gt;tefillot&lt;/em&gt;, meals, and all other aspects of communal life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support teen transportation to/from the airport and/or train station, including greeting at the airport/train station and riding buses to/from the hotel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow and enforce all health and safety guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete nightly room checks to ensure teen safety and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Programming&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support staff, designated teens, and other madrichim with programming efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and facilitate informal education programming (athletics, electives, skill builders, Shabbat).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with preparing program materials and spaces as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creatively flip spaces to build immersive experiences and pop-up environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the community healthy, happy, focused, and enthusiastic to deliver a memorable experience. Execute role with the highest level of customer service and participant care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide comfort, support, and compassion for all participants during program duration.&lt;/li&gt;
