&lt;p&gt;At BBYO, we&#39;re motivated by our mission, inspiring us to reimagine work to make it fun, flexible, and fulfilling. We&#39;re looking for an organized, detail-oriented Operations Associate to join our team and help power the day-to-day operations of BBYO Eastern Canada.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity to play a vital role behind the scenes of one of the world&#39;s leading Jewish youth organizations. Working closely with our Executive Director and regional staff, you&#39;ll help ensure our programs, events, systems, and operations run smoothly—allowing regional staff to focus on what matters most: building meaningful relationships with Jewish teens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BBYO Eastern Canada engages more than 1,000 Jewish teens each year through chapters, leadership programs, conventions, travel experiences, and community events across Ontario and Quebec. As Operations Associate, you&#39;ll support the systems and processes that make those experiences possible. From registrations and financial administration to CRM management and process improvement, you&#39;ll play a key role in creating exceptional experiences for teens, families, volunteers, donors, alumni, and community partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you&#39;re early in your career or looking to apply your organizational talents in a mission-driven environment, this is an opportunity to grow professionally while making a lasting impact on Jewish teens. The ideal candidate is proactive, highly organized, enjoys building efficient systems, and takes pride in creating exceptional experiences for others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SHAPING THE FUTURE FOR TEENS AND YOURSELF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Operations Associate, your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing registration processes for conventions, travel experiences, leadership programs, community events, and other organizational activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining registration forms, participant records, waivers, payments, and event communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing participant lists, nametags, rooming lists, dietary reports, transportation manifests, health and emergency information, and other event materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating day-to-day administrative operations while supporting organizational projects, initiatives, and strategic priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing, documenting, and improving organizational processes, workflows, templates, and standard operating procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining accurate membership, prospect, alumni, donor, volunteer, and program participation records within the organization&#39;s CRM and databases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Producing reports and dashboards to inform organizational planning, recruitment, fundraising, and program evaluation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing invoices, reimbursements, deposits, expense claims, and other financial documentation while assisting with budget tracking and financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Processing memberships, registrations, donations, and other organizational payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying opportunities to improve efficiency through better systems, automation, and operational workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining digital filing systems, organizational templates, shared resources, and institutional knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serving as a primary point of contact for administrative inquiries from teens, parents, volunteers, alumni, donors, and community partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
